The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional neural networks (DCNN) for medical imaging tasks, specifically 3D segmentation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of sparse and binary convolutions to reduce computational demands, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of these techniques for mobile devices, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
